<h2>New York Incentives & Rebates</h2>
<p>New York offers some of the nation's most comprehensive incentive programs for solar and energy efficiency improvements, beginning with the federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) that provides a 30% credit on total solar installation costs through 2032. This credit applies to equipment, installation, and associated costs, with no cap on the credit amount for residential installations. Homeowners can claim this credit on their federal tax return, and any unused credit can be rolled forward to subsequent tax years.</p>

<p>The NY-Sun Initiative, administered by NYSERDA (New York State Energy Research and Development Authority), provides additional state-level incentives for solar installations. While the program has transitioned away from direct rebates in most areas due to market maturity, it continues supporting community solar projects and low-to-moderate income programs. The initiative also funds solar training programs and workforce development, helping maintain a skilled installer base that keeps costs competitive.</p>

<p>Consolidated Edison offers several programs benefiting both solar and HVAC improvements, including the Energy Efficiency Programs that provide rebates for high-efficiency HVAC equipment, smart thermostats, and insulation upgrades. Their net metering program allows solar customers to receive full retail credit for excess electricity sent to the grid, maximizing solar savings. Additionally, ConEd's Time-of-Use rates can benefit solar customers who shift electricity usage to align with solar production periods.</p>

<p>Property tax exemptions represent another significant benefit, as New York exempts the added value from solar installations from property tax assessments for 15 years. This exemption can save homeowners hundreds to thousands of dollars annually while the solar system increases home value. Local utilities may also offer additional programs, such as PSEG Long Island's solar rebates and National Grid's energy efficiency incentives, which vary by service territory.</p>

